Cell[TextData[{
 "There is clearly a positive association in that greater height implies \
greater weight. This is also emphasized by the regression line estimated in \
(b).\n\nSolution to (e):\n(e) Add the following two points to the scatter \
plot ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    SubscriptBox["x", "18"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "570ff735-661b-4879-9168-1de781db22dd"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["y", "18"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c5933afd-46a4-4d7f-ba7f-e560cb705010"],
 ") = (175, 55) and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    SubscriptBox["x", "19"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b05dc1d1-729e-479b-8656-0a8905ede2ce"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["y", "19"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5fc2e9ea-7ab0-4aa9-b88f-2fd458af1877"],
 ") = (150, 75). Speculate how the linear regression estimate will change \
after adding these points."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9482410225151243`*^9, 
  3.948241068244813*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"96b273fb-e7ce-45a8-8b8b-\
